Choco is a java library for constraint satisfaction problems (CSP) and constraint programming (CP).
It is built on a event-based propagation mechanism with backtrackable structures.
Choco is an open-source software, distributed under a BSD License and hosted by sourceforge.net.

Main authors are Charles Prud'homme, Xavier Lorca and Jean-Guillaume Fages (Ecole des Mines de Nantes, France).
Major contributors are Hadrien Cambazard (INP Grenoble France) and Arnaud Malapert (Universit√© Nice Sophia Antipolis, France).

For any informations visit our website : http://choco.emn.fr.